---
import BaseLayout from "@/layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import PageHeader from "@/components/sections/PageHeader.astro";
import Container from "@/components/ui/Container.astro";
import { SITE_CONFIG } from "@/lib/constants";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Terms of Service | Quickfire Firewood"
  description="Terms of Service for Quickfire Firewood. Read our terms and conditions for purchasing premium Western Ironbark firewood in Brisbane and Gold Coast."
  keywords={["terms of service", "terms and conditions", "Quickfire Firewood terms", "firewood purchase terms"]}
>
  <PageHeader
    title="Terms of Service"
    subtitle="Terms and conditions for purchasing from Quickfire Firewood"
    compact={true}
  />

  <section class="py-16 lg:py-24 bg-base-100">
    <Container size="narrow">
      <p class="text-base-content/60 mb-8">
        <strong>Last updated:</strong> February 2026
      </p>

      <div class="prose prose-lg max-w-none">
        <p>
          These Terms of Service ("Terms") govern your purchase of firewood products and
          services from Quickfire Firewood ("we", "us", or "our"). By placing an order with
          us, you agree to be bound by these Terms.
        </p>

        <h2>1. About Us</h2>
        <p>
          Quickfire Firewood is a family-owned business supplying premium Western Ironbark
          firewood in Brisbane, Gold Coast, and surrounding areas of South East Queensland.
        </p>
        <p>
          <strong>Contact Details:</strong><br />
          Phone: {SITE_CONFIG.phone}<br />
          Email: {SITE_CONFIG.email}
        </p>

        <h2>2. Products</h2>

        <h3>2.1 Product Description</h3>
        <p>We supply premium Western Ironbark firewood. All firewood is:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Sustainably sourced</li>
          <li>Seasoned for a minimum of 12 months</li>
          <li>Split to customer specifications where requested</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>2.2 Product Variations</h3>
        <p>
          As firewood is a natural product, there may be minor variations in:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>Individual piece sizes within specified ranges</li>
          <li>Exact weight of orders</li>
          <li>Bark coverage and appearance</li>
        </ul>
        <p>These natural variations do not constitute defects.</p>

        <h2>3. Ordering</h2>

        <h3>3.1 Placing Orders</h3>
        <p>Orders can be placed by:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Phone: {SITE_CONFIG.phone}</li>
          <li>Email: {SITE_CONFIG.email}</li>
          <li>Website contact form</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>3.2 Order Confirmation</h3>
        <p>An order is confirmed when we have:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Agreed on quantity, pricing, and specifications</li>
          <li>Confirmed delivery or pickup arrangements</li>
          <li>Received payment or agreed payment terms</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>3.3 Order Accuracy</h3>
        <p>
          You are responsible for ensuring your order details are correct, including:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>Quantity required</li>
          <li>Split size preferences</li>
          <li>Delivery address</li>
          <li>Contact details</li>
          <li>Access requirements for delivery</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>4. Pricing and Payment</h2>

        <h3>4.1 Pricing</h3>
        <p>Prices are quoted at the time of ordering and may vary based on:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Quantity ordered</li>
          <li>Delivery location</li>
          <li>Current market conditions</li>
        </ul>
        <p>
          All prices are quoted in Australian Dollars (AUD) and include GST where applicable.
        </p>

        <h3>4.2 Delivery Charges</h3>
        <p>
          Delivery charges are additional to product prices and depend on delivery location,
          order size, and access requirements. Delivery charges will be confirmed at the
          time of ordering.
        </p>

        <h3>4.3 Payment Methods</h3>
        <p>We accept:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Cash on delivery</li>
          <li>Credit/debit card</li>
          <li>Bank transfer</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>4.4 Payment Terms</h3>
        <p>
          For residential orders, payment is required at the time of delivery or pickup
          unless otherwise arranged. For commercial accounts, payment terms may be
          negotiated on application.
        </p>

        <h2>5. Delivery</h2>

        <h3>5.1 Delivery Area</h3>
        <p>
          We deliver throughout Brisbane, Gold Coast, and surrounding areas of South East
          Queensland. Delivery availability outside our standard service area can be
          discussed on a case-by-case basis.
        </p>

        <h3>5.2 Delivery Timing</h3>
        <p>
          We will advise an estimated delivery date at the time of ordering. While we make
          every effort to meet delivery timeframes, exact delivery times cannot be guaranteed.
        </p>

        <h3>5.3 Delivery Location</h3>
        <p>
          Firewood will be delivered to a suitable location on your property that is
          accessible to our delivery vehicle and safe for unloading. We cannot deliver to
          locations that require carrying firewood significant distances or up multiple
          flights of stairs without prior arrangement.
        </p>

        <h3>5.4 Your Responsibilities</h3>
        <p>You must ensure:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Clear vehicle access to the delivery location</li>
          <li>Someone is available to receive the delivery (unless otherwise arranged)</li>
          <li>Any access codes or instructions are provided in advance</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>5.5 Stacking Service</h3>
        <p>
          Stacking services are available by request at additional cost. Please advise at
          the time of ordering if you require stacking.
        </p>

        <h2>6. Pickup</h2>
        <p>If you choose to collect your order:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Contact us to arrange a pickup time</li>
          <li>Bring appropriate transport for your order</li>
          <li>Payment is required at time of pickup unless otherwise arranged</li>
        </ul>
        <p>
          We will load your order onto your vehicle. You are responsible for securing the
          load for transport.
        </p>

        <h2>7. Cancellations and Changes</h2>

        <h3>7.1 Cancellation by Customer</h3>
        <p>If you need to cancel an order:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Contact us as soon as possible</li>
          <li>Cancellations before dispatch incur no charge</li>
          <li>Cancellations after dispatch may incur delivery charges</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>7.2 Changes to Orders</h3>
        <p>
          Changes to order quantity or specifications can be made prior to dispatch by
          contacting us.
        </p>

        <h3>7.3 Cancellation by Us</h3>
        <p>We reserve the right to cancel orders in circumstances including:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Product unavailability</li>
          <li>Delivery location inaccessible</li>
          <li>Non-payment for prior orders</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>8. Quality and Returns</h2>

        <h3>8.1 Quality Assurance</h3>
        <p>
          All firewood is inspected for quality before dispatch. Our firewood is properly
          seasoned (12+ months), suitable for burning, and split as specified.
        </p>

        <h3>8.2 Issues with Orders</h3>
        <p>If you have concerns about your order:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Contact us within 7 days of delivery</li>
          <li>Provide photos if relevant</li>
          <li>We will investigate and resolve the issue</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>8.3 Resolution</h3>
        <p>Where a genuine quality issue exists, we will at our discretion:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Replace affected firewood</li>
          <li>Provide a partial or full refund</li>
          <li>Provide credit towards future orders</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>8.4 Australian Consumer Law</h3>
        <p>
          Nothing in these Terms excludes or limits consumer guarantees under the Australian
          Consumer Law. You are entitled to a replacement or refund for a major failure and
          compensation for any other reasonably foreseeable loss or damage.
        </p>

        <h2>9. Limitation of Liability</h2>
        <p>To the extent permitted by law:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Our liability is limited to the purchase price of the goods</li>
          <li>We are not liable for indirect or consequential losses</li>
          <li>
            We are not responsible for damage caused by improper use or storage of firewood
          </li>
        </ul>

        <h2>10. Use of Firewood</h2>
        <p>You are responsible for:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Safe storage of firewood</li>
          <li>Safe use of firewood in appropriate appliances</li>
          <li>Compliance with local fire regulations and restrictions</li>
          <li>
            Ensuring firewood is used in accordance with manufacturer instructions for your
            appliance
          </li>
        </ul>

        <h2>11. Fire Safety</h2>
        <p>Firewood should only be burned:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>
            In appropriate fireplaces, wood heaters, pizza ovens, fire pits, or BBQs
          </li>
          <li>In compliance with local fire regulations</li>
          <li>With appropriate supervision</li>
          <li>When total fire bans are not in effect</li>
        </ul>
        <p>
          We are not responsible for damage or injury resulting from improper use of
          firewood.
        </p>

        <h2>12. Intellectual Property</h2>
        <p>
          All content on our website, including text, images, and logos, is owned by
          Quickfire Firewood and protected by intellectual property laws. You may not
          reproduce, distribute, or use our content without permission.
        </p>

        <h2>13. Privacy</h2>
        <p>
          Your personal information is handled in accordance with our{" "}
          <a href="/privacy-policy">Privacy Policy</a> and the Australian Privacy Act 1988.
        </p>

        <h2>14. Disputes</h2>
        <p>If you have a dispute regarding your order:</p>
        <ol>
          <li>Contact us to discuss the issue</li>
          <li>We will investigate and respond within a reasonable timeframe</li>
          <li>If we cannot resolve the dispute directly, mediation may be pursued</li>
        </ol>

        <h2>15. Governing Law</h2>
        <p>
          These Terms are governed by the laws of Queensland, Australia. Any disputes will
          be subject to the jurisdiction of Queensland courts.
        </p>

        <h2>16. Changes to Terms</h2>
        <p>
          We may update these Terms from time to time. Changes will be posted on this page
          with an updated revision date. Continued use of our services after changes
          constitutes acceptance of the updated Terms.
        </p>

        <h2>17. Contact Us</h2>
        <p>For questions about these Terms, please contact us:</p>
        <p>
          <strong>Quickfire Firewood</strong><br />
          Phone:{" "}
          <a href={SITE_CONFIG.phoneLink}>{SITE_CONFIG.phone}</a><br />
          Email:{" "}
          <a href={SITE_CONFIG.emailLink}>{SITE_CONFIG.email}</a>
        </p>

        <hr />

        <p class="text-base-content/60">Thank you for choosing Quickfire Firewood.</p>
      </div>
    </Container>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
